      "content": "thanks. that makes sense. one thing though, we've been seeing some weird behavior where sometimes the memory usage spikes unexpectedly even after we patched the obvious leaks. it's like there are these tiny, hard-to-find bits of memory being held onto in places we didn't expect. are there any other common \"hidden\" ways that memory can get stuck in a C++ loop like this? maybe something subtle that stays out of sight?",
